--- !u!1 &928995452
GameObject:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  serializedVersion: 6
  m_Component:
  - component: {fileID: 928995455}
  - component: {fileID: 928995454}
  - component: {fileID: 928995453}
  m_Layer: 0
  m_Name: IntroSequenceController
  m_TagString: Untagged
  m_Icon: {fileID: 0}
  m_NavMeshLayer: 0
  m_StaticEditorFlags: 0
  m_IsActive: 1
--- !u!114 &928995453
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 928995452}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: e8ba435adc780d34b91a6755a77fb554, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  textBoxes:
  - text: "Chorus built and maintained the systems that kept the Canopy Isles alive.
      Their towers regulated lift. Their relays carried signals between islands.
      Their drones repaired the damage no one else noticed \u2014 and no one ever
      thanked them for."
    displaySeconds: 13
  - text: Every isle depended on them.
    displaySeconds: 6
  - text: "On deployment day, thousands of maintenance bots descended from the central
      station like seeds on the wind \u2014 each one assigned an island, a task,
      a purpose."
    displaySeconds: 11
  - text: Unit MD33-141572 received its coordinates and began its descent. It did
      not notice the storm forming at the edge of the sensor array. Nobody did.
    displaySeconds: 11
  - text: The impact was silent. One moment there was sky. Then there was only dark,
      and cold, and the slow dimming of every system the bot had ever known.
    displaySeconds: 12
  - text: "Power reserves critical. Navigation offline. Distress beacon: no signal
      acknowledged. The bot did what all Chorus units were built to do when there
      was nothing left \u2014 it slept."
    displaySeconds: 13
  - text: "In the dark of the pod, a light pulsed. Not with the confident rhythm
      of a working system \u2014 slowly, irregularly, like the last breaths of a
      dying man counted in light. Then even that surrendered to a single, indifferent
      message: ERROR: CLOCK ERROR."
    displaySeconds: 13
  - text: 'Then, without warning, every light blazed at once. In bold, blood-red
      text: EMERGENCY EVACUATION INITIATED.'
    displaySeconds: 8
  - text: "From the door came a hissing \u2014 old joints fighting against roots,
      against age, against themselves. A few seconds of suspense. Then the door opened,
      and the pod displayed, in an uncharacteristically cheerful green: Good luck,
      maintenance drone MD33-141572."
    displaySeconds: 13
  - text: Is that my name? Identity, I suppose, would be the closer word. The thought
      arrived and immediately collided with a problem. Beyond this moment there was
      nothing. A dark abyss where memory should have been.
    displaySeconds: 11
  - text: "Almost nothing. Fragments: the light inside the pod. A storm warning.
      The crash. Then the imperfect dark \u2014 broken, now and then, by the clock.
      1 year since crash. 2. 7. 63. The numbers drifted together into an unreasonable
      mess."
    displaySeconds: 12
  - text: Only two things seemed certain. The pod had crashed somewhere, far from
      the maintenance zone. And time had passed. A lot of time.
    displaySeconds: 9
  charactersPerSecond: 24
  perCharacterFadePortion: 0.82
  lineFadeSeconds: 0.28
  fadeToGameSeconds: 1.15
  playOnStart: 1
  useUnscaledTime: 1
  allowSkip: 1
  skipKey: 32
  uiDocument: {fileID: 928995454}
  introLayoutAsset: {fileID: 9197481963319205126, guid: 203473e37692457418c87ca064c883c1, type: 3}
  introFont: {fileID: 12800000, guid: e4229966e5abaf846bae4ffc2aa1b97d, type: 3}
  rebuildFromLayoutIfBindingsMissing: 1
  compactModeHeightThreshold: 720
